Introduction

Looking at the monocle trajectory of the progenitors. Also looking at it when including MKs and ERYs. Following previous work done on monocle and following the vignette

Checking of the Pseudotime Ordering

In the example they look at proliferation genes (Ccnb2, Myod1, Myog) and see how theyre expressed over pseudotime. This also checks to see if the pseudotime is reversed or not.

These genes made sense for the example, but we should figure out our own (looking at the marker genes weve been using to distinguish progenitors).
